“We are very close to returning to the Pacific Ocean,” he promised last August.
However, some analysts think that it is unlikely that the Court will decide in favor of Bolivia and that, if it did, things would not change much.
The U.N. body based in the Netherlands has no authority to allocate Chilean territory and has stated that it will not determine the outcome of the possible talks.
