Ri did not refer to plans to hold a second summit between Kim and Trump that the U.S. leader highlighted at the United Nations earlier this week.
Instead, the minister highlighted three meetings between Kim and South Korean leader Moon Jae-in in the past five months and added: “If the party involved in the denuclearization issue were South Korea instead of the US, the denuclearization of the Korean peninsula would not have reached this stagnation situation.”
However, the tone of Ri’s speech was very different from last year’s, when he declared to the UN General Assembly that targeting U.S. territory with North Korean missiles was inevitable after President “Mr. Evil” Trump dubbed Kim “Rocket Man” on a suicide mission.
